<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05015b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05015b">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05015b"> 15(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> sons of God &amp; daughters</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The immediate cause of all this wickedness seems to have been the mixed marriages that took place between &ldquo;the <mark>sons of God</mark>&rdquo; and the &ldquo;<mark>daughters</mark> of men.&rdquo; These sons of God are said to have been the &ldquo;Sethites,&rdquo; and the daughters of men the &ldquo;Cainites.&rdquo; But this does not account for the peculiar offspring they engendered. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [Noah&apos;s Flood] 51</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Genesis 6:- 1 The wickedness of the world, which provoked God&apos;s wrath, and caused the flood. 8 Noah findeth grace. 14 The order, form and end of the ark. Cf. Verse 4: <i>There were giants in the earth in those days: and also after that, when the sons of God came unto the daughters of men, the same became mighty men which were of old, men of renown.</i> </mm> </dd></dl>
